Problem Statement:
A recruiter gets 100s of resume on a job post, he/she wants to do a screening to get the most qualified and suited individuals as quickly as possible. Moreover, a recruiter is working on multiple positions at a time.
User:
A user gets a folder with 100 resumes for one role and is working on several hirings. He/ She wants to shortlist candidates under 30 minutes, so they could save time by not reading resumes that are not even related.
Goals & Success Metrics:
A user uploads a resume and get important data extracted in a spreadsheet with more than 90% accuracy, the sheet is ready to be used as it has data and the comments about the candidates about their status.
In scope/ Out of Scope:
•	Upload pdf file 
•	Extract correct Information in Spreadsheet
•	It returns the reason why some candidate is shortlisted or rejected.
•	Different criteria like location, expected salary, relevant technical skills have weightage in overall calculation of score in order to shortlist/reject a candidate.
•	Sheet is download able.
Key risks:
•	The information is not extracted properly.
•	It overlooks some important information that can reject actually capable candidates.
What’s done look like:
I upload resumes in bulk and it provide me a ready to use excel sheet that has data for all the candidates. It should also give me a list of shortlisted candidates in order starts from best, and write a reason why this candidate is useful/ or reject.

